Michael Brelo is charged with voluntary manslaughter in the deaths of Timothy Russell and Malissa Williams in November 2012 . 
  The 31-year-old jumped on the hood of a Chevy Malibu and fired 15 shots . 
  He is the only officer charged because he waited until after other officers had stopped shooting to fire the last of 49 rounds . 
  His attorney said he had reason to believe he was being shot at . 
  Timothy Russell , 43 , and Williams , 30 were unarmed when they were killed . 
 